# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The code implements a sliding window approach to find the maximum number of vowels in a substring of length k in a given string. It uses a variable sum to keep track of the number of vowels in the current window and updates it at each step by adding the vowel count of the new character and subtracting the vowel count of the character that has just left the window. It also keeps track of the maximum sum seen so far in a variable ans and returns it at the end of the loop.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(1)
![download (15).jfif](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/98d5121b-bd68-45d5-88cf-963020d28768_1683259142.9221802.jpeg)
