# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The main logic of this problem is that for a pseudo-palindromic path
the path must contain **atmost one odd occurence of an element**.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We will be doing normal dfs and at the same time we'll store the frequency of the elements in a map. At the leaf node we'll just check the condition for pseudo-palindromic path and increment our answer.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(n) --> n is the no of nodes in tree

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(k) --> k is the no of distinct elements in path from root node  to deepest leaf node. 

# Code
