solutions.content:
As we are given to check if path represents any permutation of palindromic sequence, we can just keep track of how many odd frequency elements are there.
As we know in a palindromic sequence there will be atmost one odd palindromic number.
So at every node of the tree we traverse, we check if that number is already repeated odd number of times or even number of times. This is done with the help of two boolean arrays, odd and even
Eg: We want to add 5 to our path, if 5 is there then boolean values of odd[5-1] and even[5-1] will be false. So to speak in converse way,
* 	if odd[k-1] and even[k-1] is false implies that this number is first time getting included in the path and after adding it odd[k-1] become true, i.e., k is repeated odd number of times (1 in this case)
* 	if odd[k-1] true implies that k has already repeated odd number of times, and including k here makes that previous count to odd so we make odd[k-1] false and even[k-1] true;
* 	if even[k-1] true implies even times occurance of element k till previous node, if we add k then it become odd number of times, so we make even[k-1] false and odd[k-1] true.

For every leaf nodes(nodes with both left and right pointers pointing to null) we check number of odd times repeated elements(for a sequence to become pseudo palindromic n(odd) should be atmost 1. We really dont bother about even frequencies.

```
class Solution {
    int ans=0;
    public int pseudoPalindromicPaths (TreeNode root) {
        //two boolean arrays for storing count
        boolean[] even = new boolean[9];
        boolean[] odd = new boolean[9];
        //Preorder traversal
        func(root,even,odd);
        return ans;
    }
    private void func(TreeNode root,boolean[] even,boolean[] odd){
        //Base case
        if(root==null){
            return;
        }
        //Main case
        //Clone boolean arrays
        boolean[] neweven = new boolean[9];
        boolean[] newodd = new boolean[9];
        for(int i=0;i<9;i++){
            neweven[i]=even[i];
            newodd[i]=odd[i];
        }
        //If this variable is not in the path
        if(!neweven[root.val-1]&&!newodd[root.val-1]){
            //Add this into odd place
            newodd[root.val-1]=true;
        }else if(!neweven[root.val-1]){
            neweven[root.val-1]=true;
            newodd[root.val-1]=false;
        }else if(!newodd[root.val-1]){
            neweven[root.val-1]=false;
            newodd[root.val-1]=true;
        }

        if(root.left==null&&root.right==null){
            //Leaf node case so update the answer
            int count=0;
            for(boolean b:newodd){
                if(b)count++;
            }
            if(count<=1)ans++;
            return;
        }

        //Calling for childs
        func(root.left,neweven,newodd);
        func(root.right,neweven,newodd);
    }
}
```

